    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-10-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="174" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <head>No. 174.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Case</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy
                                            Department</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-10-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 29,
                                        1872</date>. (Received October 30.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your letter of the 26th instant, and to inform you that
                                instructions have been sent to Commander Byron Wilson, commanding
                                the United States steamer Yantic, to co-operate with the agent of
                                Her Britannic Majesty’s government, in any proper way, to secure the
                                success of his mission to Muscat or Zanzibar.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A. LUDLOW CASE,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of
                                        the Navy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
